        <h1>About Us</h1>
      <p>Along with a support and research staff, Carlson Food Careers has a winning combination that presents our candidates in a professional and confidential manner to our multi-national clients.   Our success is based on developing personal relationships which are built on honesty, integrity and a high level of customer service.  As a result we have placed hundreds of people in new positions, most of which are still in those positions leading successful careers.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>30+ Years Professional Experience in:</strong></li>
        <li>Ingredient Sales</li>
        <li>Product Development</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Education:</strong></li>
        <li>MS - Food Chemistry</li>
        <li>BS - Microbiology</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Prior to starting Carlson Food Careers recruiting company, Van Carlson was Vice President of Midwest Accounts for DRAGOCO, Inc., a multi-national flavor and fragrance manufacturer. At DRAGOCO, he was part of a technical and sales team that built a territory from zero to $14 million in domestic sales and was a valuable partner and preferred supplier with seven of the top 25 food companies in the U.S. This required a close working relationship with: product development, process engineers, packaging development and the supply chain organization which included production, operations, customer service, purchasing and marketing.</p>
      <p>Earlier in Van’s career, he was a new product and process developer for both Pillsbury and Archer Daniels Midland. Leading projects from concept through commercialization has given him invaluable insight into the staffing needs of food manufacturers.</p>
      <p class="testimonial">“I am so grateful to you that you were so patient and reassuring with me through this whole process.  You have a real talent for matching people with great companies with a range of options: company culture, industry expertise, locations, etc. You have a great team and I will always do whatever I can to further your success.” <br />
      <em>- Placed Candidate</em></p>
